I"/<p>Test any changes to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file before launching Open Peer Power. This script allows you to test changes without the need to restart Open Peer Power.</p>
<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">$ hass --script check_config</code></pre></figure>
<p>The script has further options like checking configuration files which are not located in the default directory or showing your secrets for debugging.</p>
<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">$ hass --script check_config -h
usage: hass [-h] [--script {check_config}] [-c CONFIG] [-i [INFO]] [-f] [-s]
<p>Check Open Peer Power configuration.</p>
<p>optional arguments:
-h, –help            show this help message and exit
–script {check_config}
-c CONFIG, –config CONFIG
Directory that contains the Open Peer Power
configuration
-i [INFO], –info [INFO]
Show a portion of the config
-f, –files           Show used configuration files
-s, –secrets         Show secret information</code></pre></figure></p>
